On these peers, see CXIV. 3 and 5. The encomium here must be confessed to over- shoot the mark; but, though a poet, Johnston was no prophet, and little discerned the grim decapitation scene awaiting the former [the Marquis] after Preston, in March, 1649.

ARGUMENT.

What age can fail to mark the Hamiltons’ renown, a race that has given two Phoenixesl to the world? One fulminates victorious in Germany: the

other directs the sceptre of justice at home. Give back, ye Muses, old Homer: another Achilles has returned; another wise Ulysses springs anew in Seotland.

1This encomium has been applied to Arthur Johnston himself and his brother as two Phoenixes.
